President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Bonnie A. Barsamian as a member of the Board of Directors of the Securities Investor Protection Corporation. Barsamian is currently a partner at Baker Botts L.L.P in New York. She has also served as Special Counsel at Fried, Frank, Harris, Shriver & Jacobson LLP and was a partner at Dechert LLP. Barsamian has held volunteer roles at Amherst College and received a B.A. from Amherst College and a J.D. from the University of Chicago Law School.

President Obama has also announced his intent to appoint Joyce St. Clair as a member of the Advisory Committee to the Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation. St. Clair is currently the Chief Capital Management Officer at Northern Trust and has held various management positions at the company since 1992. She was previously an Associate Partner at Andersen Consulting (now Accenture) and has served as a Director of Northern Trust Fund Services (Ireland) Limited and Northern Trust Investor Services (Ireland) Limited. St. Clair received a B.S. from Indiana University and an M.B.A. from the University of Chicago.